Fulton County Judge Jerry Baxter urged the defendants during the sentencing hearing on Monday to accept deals or face significantly more time behind bars .
If the convicted educators accept deals, they would be required to apologize and waive their right to appeal .
Prosecutors accused the defendants of erasing incorrect answers or instructing students to change their answers so they could secure promotions or bonuses .
A total of 35 Atlanta educators were indicted in March 2013 on charges including racketeering, making false statements and theft .